Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Failing test: "should return premium 165 G for newcomer with cursed sword (steel, enchantment 3) — 100 base + 50 curse + 10 first insurance = 160 + 5 fee = 165"
Expected behavior: Cursed items get a 50% surcharge on their base premium. This is an item-specific modifier.
Current error: Expected 165, received 115
Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
const FIRST_INSURANCE_RATE = 0.1;

const BASE_PREMIUM: Record<string, number> = {
  sword: 100, amulet: 60, staff: 80, potion: 40, rune: 25, moonstone: 25,
};

const COMPONENT_TYPES = new Set(["rune", "moonstone"]);
const BLOCK_SIZE = 3;
const BLOCK_PREMIUM = 60;

function countByType(items: any[]): Record<string, number> {
  const counts: Record<string, number> = {};
  for (const item of items) {
    counts[item.type] = (counts[item.type] ?? 0) + 1;
  }
  return counts;
}

function calculateBasePremium(typeCounts: Record<string, number>): number {
  let total = 0;
  for (const [type, count] of Object.entries(typeCounts)) {
    if (COMPONENT_TYPES.has(type) && count === BLOCK_SIZE) {
      total += BLOCK_PREMIUM;
    } else {
      total += count * (BASE_PREMIUM[type] ?? 0);
    }
  }
  return total;
}

function calculateQuotePremium(items: any[]): number {
  const typeCounts = countByType(items);
  const basePremium = calculateBasePremium(typeCounts);
  const firstInsurance = basePremium * FIRST_INSURANCE_RATE;
  return Math.ceil(basePremium + firstInsurance + PROCESSING_FEE);
}

export function processScenario(scenario: any): unknown {
  const results = scenario.steps.map((step: any) => ({
    premium: calculateQuotePremium(step.items),
  }));
  return { results };
}
```

The premium formula should be:
- policy base premium = sum of all item base premiums (from calculateBasePremium)
- item surcharges = sum of per-item surcharges (cursed = 50% of that item's base premium)
- policy-wide surcharges = first insurance = 10% of policy base premium
- total = policy base premium + item surcharges + policy-wide surcharges + processing fee

The cursed surcharge applies per item, so we need to iterate items and check the cursed flag. For this test: sword base = 100, curse surcharge = 50% of 100 = 50. Policy base = 100. First insurance = 10% of 100 = 10. Total = 100 + 50 + 10 + 5 = 165.

Minimal approach: add a function to calculate item-specific surcharges (just cursed for now), and add it to the premium calculation.

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

